Fishing boats bob gently, their white hulls now transformed to pearl-gray in the dimming light, while their masts stand like thin brushstrokes of midnight blue against the still-glowing sky.

In the foreground, a cluster of lobster pots creates a rich composition of deep burgundy and forest green, their ropes trailing like dark licorice against the weathered dock. The warm ochre of the lighthouse peels slightly, revealing layers of golden yellow beneath, while its beacon cuts through the gathering dusk in sharp wedges of electric blue-white.

The overall palette whispers of endings and beginnings—the passionate reds and oranges of day's final breath gradually surrendering to the cool purples and navy blues of approaching night, creating a visual symphony where warmth and coolness dance in perfect tension.
